OL,3,GOPINIONCWhen playout goes badly wrong
OL,4,
OL,5,FTonight's playout error on BBC One
OL,6,FScotland is right up there with the
OL,7,Fmost serious we can recall by a BBC
OL,8,FPresentation department.
OL,10,FEven the most inexperienced of hospital
OL,11,Fradio broadcasters know a simple rule `
OL,12,Ftreat every microphone or studio as if
OL,13,Fit were live. But it's a rule that's
OL,14,Feasy to ignore.
OL,16,FImagine if something unfortunate or
OL,17,Funexpected ` however innocent ` had
OL,18,Fhappened when The One Show studio was
OL,19,Faccidentally put to air. A naughty
OL,20,Fword, a friendly joke at the expense of
OL,21,Fthe floor manager ` or something far
OL,22,Fworse.
OL,23,EPub: 18-Mar-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,148,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14702
SC,0002
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F147A1776604038
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/7
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCWhen playout goes badly wrong
OL,4,
OL,5,FJust think of the field day the
OL,6,Fnewspapers would have. Potentially
OL,7,Fmaking national headlines.
OL,9,FThen there is the question of the loss
OL,10,Fof part of the BBC News at Six. That
OL,11,Fcannot be taken lightly.
OL,13,FMistakes are an inevitable part of live
OL,14,Fbroadcasting. What is harder to
OL,15,Funderstand is why this error was not
OL,16,Fcorrected far sooner.
OL,18,FThe announcer/director on duty
OL,19,Fshould've had the option of taking the
OL,20,Fcontinuity desk out of circuit and
OL,21,Freturning to the network feed. Why was
OL,22,Fthat not done more promptly?
OL,23,EPub: 18-Mar-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,148,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14703
SC,0003
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F147A1776604038
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/7
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCWhen playout goes badly wrong
OL,4,
OL,5,FIt's not for us to speculate on how the
OL,6,Ferror occurred but it should be taken
OL,7,Fseriously.
OL,9,FBBC announcer/directors in the nations
OL,10,Fdo a complex job and usually do it very
OL,11,Fwell. Often they don't get the credit
OL,12,Fthey deserve. But errors like this one
OL,13,Frisk undermining the reputation of the
OL,14,FBBC itself.
OL,23,EPub: 18-Mar-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
